The paper deals with the problem of decentralized scheduling in Interference Channels, which involves communication and networking (cs.NI) as well as information theory (cs.IT). The proposed solution involves the use of Collaborative Deep Neural Networks (C-DNNs), which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the problem of decentralized scheduling can be seen as a control problem (cs.SY) where each transmitter makes a decision based on feedback from the environment. Therefore, cs.SY is also a likely sub-category.
